HEADWORD: hospitalise
<hw>hos"pi*tal*ise</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To place (a
person) in a hospital in order to receive medical treatment, for
observation, or for rest.</def> <mark>[Chiefly Brit.]</mark> ⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> hospitalize.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

